title: Britannica yearbook 1913 Brockhaus 1897
description:
The Brockhaus supplement is an A-Z one , and by learning how it is said in 

   german things like "population" , "importations" , "number of war ships" 

   and the like is possible to get several good data.




   Example: The article Algeria starts this way:




   "Algerien hatte 1891 4.124.732 Einwohner , darunter 271.101 Franzossen und

   47.564 Juden"





-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------




   Do not download the Atlas of World Population (Mc Evedy) if not interested in.
